title: shadcn\par
description: Use the shadcn CLI to add components to your project.\par
---\par
\par
## init\par
\par
Use the `init` command to initialize configuration and dependencies for an existing project, or create a new project with `--name`.\par
\par
The `init` command installs dependencies, adds the `cn` util and configures CSS variables for the project.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest init\par
```\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn init [options] [components...]\par
\par
initialize your project and install dependencies\par
\par
Arguments:\par
  components                 names, url or local path to component\par
\par
Options:\par
  -t, --template <template>  the template to use. (next, vite, start, react-router, laravel, astro)\par
  -b, --base <base>          the component library to use. (radix, base)\par
  -p, --preset [name]        use a preset configuration\par
  -y, --yes                  skip confirmation prompt. (default: true)\par
  -d, --defaults             use default configuration: --template=next --preset=nova (default: false)\par
  -f, --force                force overwrite of existing configuration. (default: false)\par
  -c, --cwd <cwd>            the working directory. defaults to the current directory.\par
  -n, --name <name>          the name for the new project.\par
  -s, --silent               mute output. (default: false)\par
  --css-variables            use css variables for theming. (default: true)\par
  --no-css-variables         do not use css variables for theming.\par
  --monorepo                 scaffold a monorepo project.\par
  --no-monorepo              skip the monorepo prompt.\par
  --rtl                      enable RTL support.\par
  --no-rtl                   disable RTL support.\par
  --pointer                  enable pointer cursor for buttons.\par
  --no-pointer               disable pointer cursor for buttons.\par
  --reinstall                re-install existing UI components.\par
  --no-reinstall             do not re-install existing UI components.\par
  -h, --help                 display help for command\par
```\par
\par
The `create` command is an alias for `init`:\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest create\par
```\par
\par
---\par
\par
## add\par
\par
Use the `add` command to add components and dependencies to your project.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest add [component]\par
```\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn add [options] [components...]\par
\par
add a component to your project\par
\par
Arguments:\par
  components           name, url or local path to component\par
\par
Options:\par
  -y, --yes            skip confirmation prompt. (default: false)\par
  -o, --overwrite      overwrite existing files. (default: false)\par
  -c, --cwd <cwd>      the working directory. defaults to the current directory.\par
  -a, --all            add all available components (default: false)\par
  -p, --path <path>    the path to add the component to.\par
  -s, --silent         mute output. (default: false)\par
  --dry-run            preview changes without writing files. (default: false)\par
  --diff [path]        show diff for a file.\par
  --view [path]        show file contents.\par
  -h, --help           display help for command\par
```\par
\par
---\par
\par
## apply\par
\par
Use the `apply` command to apply a preset to an existing project.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest apply a2r6bw\par
```\par
\par
You can apply only the theme or fonts from a preset without reinstalling UI components:\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest apply a2r6bw --only theme\par
```\par
\par
Supported values for `--only` are `theme` and `font`.\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn apply [options] [preset]\par
\par
apply a preset to an existing project\par
\par
Arguments:\par
  preset             the preset to apply\par
\par
Options:\par
  --preset <preset>  preset configuration to apply\par
  --only [parts]     apply only parts of a preset: theme, font\par
  -y, --yes          skip confirmation prompt. (default: false)\par
  -c, --cwd <cwd>    the working directory. defaults to the current directory.\par
  -s, --silent       mute output. (default: false)\par
  -h, --help         display help for command\par
```\par
\par
---\par
\par
## preset\par
\par
Use the `preset` command to inspect preset codes and resolve the preset for an existing project.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest preset decode a2r6bw\par
```\par
\par
### preset decode\par
\par
Use `preset decode` to decode a preset code.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest preset decode a2r6bw\par
```\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn preset decode [options] <code>\par
\par
decode a preset code\par
\par
Arguments:\par
  code        the preset code to decode\par
\par
Options:\par
  --json      output as JSON. (default: false)\par
  -h, --help  display help for command\par
```\par
\par
### preset resolve\par
\par
Use `preset resolve` to resolve the preset from the current project.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest preset resolve\par
```\par
\par
The `preset info` command is an alias for `preset resolve`:\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest preset info\par
```\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn preset resolve|info [options]\par
\par
resolve a preset from your project\par
\par
Options:\par
  -c, --cwd <cwd>  the working directory. defaults to the current directory.\par
  --json            output as JSON. (default: false)\par
  -h, --help        display help for command\par
```\par
\par
### preset url\par
\par
Use `preset url` to print the create URL for a preset code.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest preset url a2r6bw\par
```\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn preset url [options] <code>\par
\par
get the create URL for a preset code\par
\par
Arguments:\par
  code        the preset code\par
\par
Options:\par
  -h, --help  display help for command\par
```\par
\par
### preset open\par
\par
Use `preset open` to open a preset code in the browser.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest preset open a2r6bw\par
```\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn preset open [options] <code>\par
\par
open a preset code in the browser\par
\par
Arguments:\par
  code        the preset code\par
\par
Options:\par
  -h, --help  display help for command\par
```\par
\par
