\par
## view\par
\par
Use the `view` command to view items from the registry before installing them.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest view [item]\par
```\par
\par
You can view multiple items at once:\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest view button card dialog\par
```\par
\par
Or view items from namespaced registries:\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest view @acme/auth @v0/dashboard\par
```\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn view [options] <items...>\par
\par
view items from the registry\par
\par
Arguments:\par
  items            the item names or URLs to view\par
\par
Options:\par
  -c, --cwd <cwd>  the working directory. defaults to the current directory.\par
  -h, --help       display help for command\par
```\par
\par
---\par
\par
## search\par
\par
Use the `search` command to search for items from registries.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest search [registry]\par
```\par
\par
You can search with a query:\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest search @shadcn -q "button"\par
```\par
\par
Or search multiple registries at once:\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest search @shadcn @v0 @acme\par
```\par
\par
The `list` command is an alias for `search`:\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest list @acme\par
```\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn search|list [options] <registries...>\par
\par
search items from registries\par
\par
Arguments:\par
  registries             the registry names or urls to search items from. Names\par
                         must be prefixed with @.\par
\par
Options:\par
  -c, --cwd <cwd>        the working directory. defaults to the current directory.\par
  -q, --query <query>    query string\par
  -l, --limit <number>   maximum number of items to display per registry (default: "100")\par
  -o, --offset <number>  number of items to skip (default: "0")\par
  -h, --help             display help for command\par
```\par
\par
