\par
## build\par
\par
Use the `build` command to generate the registry JSON files.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest build\par
```\par
\par
This command reads the `registry.json` file and generates the registry JSON files in the `public/r` directory.\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn build [options] [registry]\par
\par
build components for a shadcn registry\par
\par
Arguments:\par
  registry             path to registry.json file (default: "./registry.json")\par
\par
Options:\par
  -o, --output <path>  destination directory for json files (default: "./public/r")\par
  -c, --cwd <cwd>      the working directory. defaults to the current directory.\par
  -h, --help           display help for command\par
```\par
\par
To customize the output directory, use the `--output` option.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest build --output ./public/registry\par
```\par
\par
