\par
## migrate\par
\par
Use the `migrate` command to run migrations on your project.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest migrate [migration]\par
```\par
\par
**Available Migrations**\par
\par
| Migration | Description                                             |\par
| --------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |\par
| `icons`   | Migrate your UI components to a different icon library. |\par
| `radix`   | Migrate to radix-ui.                                    |\par
| `rtl`     | Migrate your components to support RTL (right-to-left). |\par
\par
**Options**\par
\par
```bash\par
Usage: shadcn migrate [options] [migration] [path]\par
\par
run a migration.\par
\par
Arguments:\par
  migration        the migration to run.\par
  path             optional path or glob pattern to migrate.\par
\par
Options:\par
  -c, --cwd <cwd>  the working directory. defaults to the current directory.\par
  -l, --list       list all migrations. (default: false)\par
  -y, --yes        skip confirmation prompt. (default: false)\par
  -h, --help       display help for command\par
```\par
\par
---\par
\par
### migrate rtl\par
\par
The `rtl` migration transforms your components to support RTL (right-to-left) languages.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest migrate rtl\par
```\par
\par
This will:\par
\par
1. Update `components.json` to set `rtl: true`\par
2. Transform physical CSS properties to logical equivalents (e.g., `ml-4` \f1\u8594?\f0  `ms-4`, `text-left` \f1\u8594?\f0  `text-start`)\par
3. Add `rtl:` variants where needed (e.g., `space-x-4` \f1\u8594?\f0  `space-x-4 rtl:space-x-reverse`)\par
\par
**Migrate specific files**\par
\par
You can migrate specific files or use glob patterns:\par
\par
```bash\par
# Migrate a specific file\par
npx shadcn@latest migrate rtl src/components/ui/button.tsx\par
\par
# Migrate files matching a glob pattern\par
npx shadcn@latest migrate rtl "src/components/ui/**"\par
```\par
\par
If no path is provided, the migration will transform all files in your `ui` directory (from `components.json`).\par
\par
---\par
\par
### migrate radix\par
\par
The `radix` migration updates your imports from individual `@radix-ui/react-*` packages to the unified `radix-ui` package.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest migrate radix\par
```\par
\par
This will:\par
\par
1. Transform imports from `@radix-ui/react-*` to `radix-ui`\par
2. Add the `radix-ui` package to your `package.json`\par
\par
**Before**\par
\par
```tsx\par
import * as DialogPrimitive from "@radix-ui/react-dialog"\par
import * as SelectPrimitive from "@radix-ui/react-select"\par
```\par
\par
**After**\par
\par
```tsx\par
import \{ Dialog as DialogPrimitive, Select as SelectPrimitive \} from "radix-ui"\par
```\par
\par
**Migrate specific files**\par
\par
You can migrate specific files or use glob patterns:\par
\par
```bash\par
# Migrate a specific file.\par
npx shadcn@latest migrate radix src/components/ui/dialog.tsx\par
\par
# Migrate files matching a glob pattern.\par
npx shadcn@latest migrate radix "src/components/ui/**"\par
```\par
\par
If no path is provided, the migration will transform all files in your `ui` directory (from `components.json`).\par
\par
Once complete, you can remove any unused `@radix-ui/react-*` packages from your `package.json`.\lang10\par
}
